# Testing

## Framework

- Use Node's built-in test runner: `import { test } from "node:test"` and `import assert from "node:assert/strict"`.
- No Jest, no Vitest, no Mocha. The runner is invoked by `npm test`.

## No brand names in fixtures

- Test names, variable names, and string fixtures must never reference a real company, product, regulation, or country.
- Use shape-based names: `highRiskFintech`, `contentPlatform`, `friendlyTerms`, `aggressiveTerms`, `genericProvider`.
- If you need a representative ToS clause, paraphrase into neutral language or invent a placeholder operator name like "the provider".

## Three-layer testing strategy

- **Layer 1 - unit**: pure functions (rubric, sanitiser, keyword guards, label resolver). Lives in `tests/*.test.js`.
- **Layer 2 - AI-output replay**: each JSON in `tests/fixtures/ai-outputs/` is a captured or hand-authored `(documentText, rawAiResponse)` pair plus the `expectedFlags` and `expectedCredits` the pipeline should produce after every guard. `tests/analyze-pipeline.test.js` and `npm run eval` exercise the entire `parseAndValidate` path in pure Node without Chrome.
- **Layer 3 - real Chrome end-to-end**: manual, slow, only when you need to verify the live on-device model. See `TESTING.md`.

## Coverage targets

- Every new category in `rubric/categories.js` requires a rubric test asserting its weight and at least one positive plus one negative keyword-guard test.
- Every pipeline step gains a unit test for happy path and one degenerate input.
- Every bug reported from a real Chrome session lands a Layer-2 fixture under `tests/fixtures/ai-outputs/regression-*.json` before the fix is merged. The fix and the fixture ship in the same commit.
- Adding a new flag or credit category requires extending the synthetic ToS corpus in `tests/fixtures/synthetic-tos/corpus.json` so the calibration test keeps the band distribution honest.

## AI-output fixture shape

```json
{
  "name": "regression-short-id",
  "description": "what this fixture exercises",
  "documentText": "the text fed to the on-device model",
  "rawAiResponse": "the verbatim string the model returned",
  "expectedFlags": [{ "category": "...", "severity": "..." }],
  "expectedCredits": [{ "category": "..." }],
  "expectedReason": "why the pipeline should produce the above"
}
```

Never include real brand names in fixture names, descriptions, or invented document text. Real `documentText` captured from a live page may contain brand names verbatim - that is the only acceptable place.
